# mention
## 1.1: make reference to, bring up, name, note

  *  "His name was mentioned in connection with the invention."
  *  "She mentioned committee's plans with a touch of skepticism."
  *  "The director causally mentioned his dissappointment to his assistant."
  *  "The professor mentioned that the class will be canceled due to lack of enrollment."
  *  "It should be mentioned that it is wise to use up the can before puncturing it."
  *  "She mentioned that it was a fine day to go sailing."
  *  "It should be mentioned that I don't advise anyone to go blindly accepting packages from Tokyo."
